725890f-a.title: Queens: 149th Street - 14th Avenue
725890f-a.text:
149th Street, east side, at 14th Avenue, showing the White.
stone Station of the United States Post office. This intewsec
tion is known as Private McEee Square.
March 5, 1932
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725036f-a.title: Queens: 14th Avenue - 149th Street
725036f-a.text:
14th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 149th Street, showing
an old house covered with outdoor advertising. It was owned
by D. Steffens in 1873 and 1891 and at the earlier date was
known as the lInternational Hotel.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  March 5, 1932
